  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Given a positive integer N, convert it into the corresponding Excel column title.\n\nRules:\n\n1 \u2192 A\n\n2 \u2192 B\n\n\u2026\n\n26 \u2192 Z\n\n27 \u2192 AA\n\n28 \u2192 AB\n\n52 \u2192 AZ\n\n53 \u2192 BA\n\nand so on\u2026\n\nThis behaves like base-26, but with letters A\u2013Z representing 1\u201326.\n\n| Input | Output |\n| ----- | ------ |\n| 1     | A      |\n| 26    | Z      |\n| 27    | AA     |\n| 28    | AB     |\n| 37    | AK     |\n| 38    | AL     |",
